			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The bags of hay are dropped by the Millers I don't know which or if all.<BR>
But you don't get bag of hay from killing them.  They just drop a bag of<BR>
hay on the ground like you would see on any farm that produces hay.<BR>
The Millers are friendily NPC's.  I think anytime you see any of them with<BR>
a scythe you can find a bag of hay nearby. Again you don't have to kill<BR>
them for the hay.  I'm a level 18 Bard and have been hunting crows for <BR>
a long time. If you want a bag of hay give a shout when your in West Karana.<BR>
I'm sure if you're willing to part with a few gold pieces<BR>
Those of us who wander the crow feilds would be willing to<BR>
pick up a bag for you.  I normally pick em up and destory <BR>
them to increase the value of the hay. But if a player will<BR>
politely I have even given it away.  I can only get like 4cp<BR>
per bag so its not worth caring around and sell to Merchants. So, please don't spread false rumors<BR>
about the Millers having bags of Hay as loot because they actually make the hay.<BR>
